Hrm, it occurs to me that you're going to have to grapple with the possibility of having multiple keys here. The value you fetch from the oauth server looks like this:

```
{
  "keys": [
    { ... a key ... },
    { ... another key ... },
    ...
  ]
}
```

There will *almost always* be only one key in that list, but there might be more than one if the FxA server is currently doing a key rotation. The simplest way to deal with this is probably to just try each key in turn, something like:

```
keys = self.apiclient.get('/v1/jwks')['keys']
for key in keys:
    try:
        pubkey = jwt.algorithms.RSAAlgorithm.from_jwk(key)
        decoded = jwt.decode(token, pubkey, ...)
        ...etc...
    except jwt.exceptions.InvalidSignatureError:
        continue
else:
    raise WhateverErrorClassWeHaveForInvalidTokensIveForgottenTheName
```

